						<summary>

						<p>The details of date are given as Makara, śu. 2, Monday.</p>						

						<p>The inscription is mutilated. It seems to record a gift of money for offerings and worship to the deity by Sūriyaṉ Nīrēṟṟāṉ <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Rājarāja-Malaiyakularāyaṉ the same donor mentioned in No. 158 above, the Malaiyamān chief of Kiḷiyūr.</p>						

						</summary>
